Copyright 2026 the bumper authors

This product includes rule logic and metadata adapted from the following
open-source projects. The rules were re-expressed in bumper's YAML + CEL format
against the Terraform plan-JSON model; the original source is credited here.

- trivy-checks (Aqua Security) — https://github.com/aquasecurity/trivy-checks
  Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
  Check metadata (ids, severities, titles, recommended actions, CIS mappings)
  was harvested as a porting worklist (see docs/rule-catalog/).

- Checkov (Prisma Cloud / Bridgecrew) — https://github.com/bridgecrewio/checkov
  Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
  Used as a coverage cross-reference.

bumper also embeds an ADVISORY catalog (internal/catalog/) — knowledge-only
best-practice metadata (id, severity, title, resource type, remediation,
references), normalized from the projects below. These entries are not executed
against a plan; they power `bumper search` / the search_rules MCP tool.

- trivy-checks (Aqua Security) — https://github.com/aquasecurity/trivy-checks
  Apache-2.0. (see above)

- Checkov (Prisma Cloud / Bridgecrew) — https://github.com/bridgecrewio/checkov
  Apache-2.0. (see above)

- KICS (Checkmarx) — https://github.com/Checkmarx/kics
  Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
  Query metadata (severity, category, description, CWE) normalized for the
  advisory catalog.

- Prowler (Prowler Inc.) — https://github.com/prowler-cloud/prowler
  Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
  Check metadata (severity, risk, and Terraform/CLI remediation code, with
  <placeholder> tokens) normalized for the advisory catalog.

